# API BACKEND CONFIGURATION
# -------------------------
# 
# FOR VERCEL SERVERLESS BACKEND (RECOMMENDED - Option A):
# ‚úÖ DO NOT set VITE_API_URL in Vercel Dashboard ‚Üí Environment Variables
# ‚úÖ Frontend automatically uses same-origin (/api/* routing)
# ‚úÖ API available at /api/* on same domain (no CORS issues)
# ‚úÖ Cold start time: 1-3 seconds
# ‚úÖ Keep-warm: Cron jobs run every 5-10 minutes (configured in vercel.json)
# ‚úÖ This is the RECOMMENDED configuration for production deployments
#
# FOR SEPARATE BACKEND (Railway - Option B):
# ‚úÖ Set VITE_API_URL to your Railway backend URL
# ‚úÖ Example: VITE_API_URL=https://your-app.up.railway.app
# ‚ö†Ô∏è  Requires proper CORS configuration on backend
#
# FOR SEPARATE BACKEND (Render):
# ‚úÖ Set VITE_API_URL to your Render backend URL
# ‚úÖ Example: VITE_API_URL=https://your-app.onrender.com
# ‚ö†Ô∏è  Requires proper CORS configuration on backend
#
# FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (HTTP acceptable for localhost only):
# ‚úÖ Set VITE_API_URL to local backend
# ‚úÖ Example: VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# FOR PRODUCTION (HTTPS required):
# ‚úÖ Always use HTTPS for production deployments
# ‚úÖ Example: VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# Uncomment and set for local development or separate backend:
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# GUARD AGAINST UNDEFINED URLs (IMPORTANT)
# -----------------------------------------
# Set to 'true' to enforce VITE_API_URL is configured (prevents silent failures)
# ‚úÖ Recommended for development and explicit backend deployments
# ‚ùå Leave unset or 'false' for Vercel serverless (same-origin) deployments
#
# VITE_REQUIRE_BACKEND_URL=true

# OPTIONAL: Override Socket URL (only needed for separate backend deployment)
# For local development: VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:8000
# For production (HTTPS required): VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
# VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Optional: Cloudinary Configuration (for image uploads)
# VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_name

# Optional: Sendbird Configuration (for advanced messaging)
# VITE_SENDBIRD_APP_ID=your_sendbird_app_id_here

# OAuth Configuration (OPTIONAL)
# ‚ö†Ô∏è  OAuth buttons will be automatically hidden if these are not configured
# ‚ö†Ô∏è  Leave these commented out or remove them if you don't want OAuth sign-in
#
# Get Google Client ID from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
#
# Get Apple Client ID from: https://developer.apple.com/account/resources/identifiers/list/serviceId
# VITE_APPLE_CLIENT_ID=your_actual_apple_client_id_here
#
# NOTE: Do not use placeholder values like "your_google_client_id_here" or "com.hiremebahamas.signin"
# These will cause OAuth errors. Either set real values or leave the variables unset/commented out.

# =============================================================================
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# For Vercel deployments with Vercel Postgres:
# 1. Database configuration is handled automatically via Vercel Postgres integration
# 2. Backend environment variables are set in Vercel Dashboard ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
# 3. Frontend variables (VITE_*) should also be set in Vercel Dashboard
# 4. No need to set VITE_API_URL if using Vercel Serverless (api/ directory)
#
# For local development:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Set VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000 (HTTP acceptable for localhost only)
# 3. Start backend: cd ../backend && python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload
# 4. Start frontend: npm run dev
#
# For production:
# 1. Always use HTTPS URLs (e.g., VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com)
# 2. Never use HTTP for production deployments
#
# =============================================================================
